// EVENT HANDLING

EVENT HANDLING CAN BE DEFINED AS THE ACTIVITY  TAKES PLACES BY CLICKING OR PRESSING THE KEYBORD..

SOME IMPORTANT EVENT HANDLER ARE:
1) FORM EVENT: onChange   onSubmit
2)Mouse Event: onClick    onDoubleClick
3)KeyBoard Events: onKeyDown   onKeyUp  onKeyPress
4) Focus Events: onFocus   onBlur  

NORMAL FUNCTION USING THE EVENT HANDLER
 const Events=()=>{
  const handleClick=()=>{
   alert("you click the button");
  };
}

To call this..
   <button onClick={handleClick}> Click the Button</button>

FUNCTION USING THE PARAMETER
  const addtion=(a)=>{
  alert(a+10);
}

// WHENEVER WE CALL THE PARAMETRIC FUNCTION IN EVENT JHANDLING THEN WE USE CALLBACK FUNCTION

<button onClick={()=>addition(100)}> Button 2 </button>
